Quare Groove is released today. Many emails and calls with artists, deliberation over which picture to use on the cover, and it''s finally out there. Shouts to all who made it happen and those who''ve supported so far. And of course, thanks to Olan(All City Records), Yhprum, and John. Bonus: The MicroDisney track is only avai...lable on the vinyl. National Championships 2018;We had a *fantastic* weekend at the Weightlifting Ireland National Senior Championships 2018.  Despite missing some of our regulars due to flu (Cathal), a freak accident Kaie Rosborough) and the EWF Youth Coaching conference (Alex) we had a strong team of lifters representing Capital Strength Weightlifting Club. * Sari: Made 5/6 good lifts and set new Masters records in the W2 53kg category - 48kg & 65kg, 113kg total.... * Aoife: Still on the rehab train, we aimed for 6/6 good lifts, all powers & that is what we got, along with a silver medal - 66kg & 84kg, 150kg total. * Friday: Got a good nights sleep the night before (!) which helped him make 4/6 good lifts & win the national championships 105kg class- 145kg & 160kg, 305kg total * Se√°n: Made 6/6 lifts, won the National Championships and had a great weekend. Sad to see him go back to the US, but he will be back in Ireland and Capital Strength before too long! Congratulations to all who competed at the weekend and thank you to Weightlifting Ireland and all of the volunteers who made this the most successful, enjoyable & professionally run National Championships any of us can remember! text: üêß Penguins have the right idea: Both parents equally share the responsibility for raising their young. We think it‚Äôs time for us in the EU to follow suit!  Currently only one in ten EU fathers take parental leave and in certain member states men have no right to paternity leave after their child''s birth. This further widens the gender pay gap and perpetuates gender stereotypes of women as home-makers. It also means kids miss out on quality time with their dad, which is proven... to have a crucial developmental impact. Fathers taking parental and paternity leave makes sense for both parents and children, but it also makes sense for businesses! Men taking on their share of familial responsibility improves women‚Äôs workplace participation, increases morale and helps businesses retain employees. The evidence shows that where there are better conditions and paid leave, fathers take on more family responsibility. The issue of work life balance is on the European Parliament‚Äôs agenda and we want to grasp this opportunity.  We back Families Europe''s #IWantWorkLifeBalance campaign! http://socsde.ms/ZSe See more
